'''Jorrel Evan Hato''' (born 7 March 2006) is a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] or [[left-back]] for {{English football updater|Chelsea}} club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in Rotterdam, Hato moved from the youth academy of [[Sparta Rotterdam]] to [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-03-14 |title=Ajax Signs Jorrel Hato |url=https://www.ajax.nl/artikelen/ajax-contracteert-jorrel-hato/ |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=ajax.nl |language=nl}}</ref>

===Ajax===
====2022–23: Debut season====
[[File:Qarabağ vs Ajax (24.10.2024) (4) (Jorrel Hato).jpg|left|thumb|upright|Hato with [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in 2024.]]
In March 2022, Hato signed his first professional contract, keeping him with Ajax until July 2025 despite reported interest from other European clubs.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-03-15 |title=Ajax behoudt talent ondanks interesse van topclubs: 'Voel me hier op m'n best' |url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/nieuws/1022024/ajax-lijkt-topclubs-af-te-troeven-wist-direct-dat-ik-voor-ajax-zou-kiezen.html |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=VoetbalPrimeur.nl |language=nl}}</ref> As captain of the Ajax under-19 team in the [[UEFA Youth League]], he scored a notable solo goal against [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]] in October 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.patreon.com/posts/uefa-youth-md4-73292493|title=UEFA Youth League scouting MD4|website=Scouted Football}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/briljante-goal-bezorgt-tien-ajacieden-kostbaar-punt-in-youth-league|title=Briljante goal bezorgt tien Ajacieden kostbaar punt in Youth League|website=vi.nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/champions-league/youth-league/2022/10/12-98391289/youth_league_napoli_beffato_l_ajax_pareggia_all_87_
|title= Youth League, Napoli raggiunto dall'Ajax all'87'. Inter ko col Barcellona|website=Tuttosport.com}}</ref> He made his professional debut for [[Jong Ajax]] in the [[Eerste Divisie]] on 4 November 2022, coming on as a substitute against [[FC Dordrecht]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-11-04 |title=Verslag {{!}} Zeven goals in Dordrecht: Jong Ajax wint doelpuntrijk duel |url=https://www.ajax.nl/artikelen/verslag-fc-dordrecht-jong-ajax-4-november |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=www.ajax.nl |language=nl}}</ref>

On 11 January 2023, Hato made his senior competitive debut for Ajax in the [[KNVB Cup]] against [[FC Den Bosch|Den Bosch]], appearing as a second-half substitute in a 2–0 win.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=2024-03-12 |title=Contractverlenging Jorrel Hato |url=https://www.ajax.nl/artikelen/contractverlenging-jorrel-hato |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=www.ajax.nl |language=nl}}</ref> On 5 February 2023, he made his [[Eredivisie]] debut as a substitute against [[SC Cambuur]], becoming the third youngest player to debut for Ajax in the league (16 years, 335 days) behind [[Ryan Gravenberch]] and [[Clarence Seedorf]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Twomey |first=Liam |last2=Johnson |first2=Simon |last3=more |date=2025-07-30 |title=Why Chelsea want Jorrel Hato – the teenager with experience beyond his years |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6522286/2025/07/30/chelsea-jorrel-hato-analysis/ |access-date=2025-08-03 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-02-05 |title=Liveblog Cambuur – Ajax |url=https://www.ajax.nl/artikelen/liveblog-cambuur-ajax-05-02-23 |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=www.ajax.nl |language=nl-NL}}</ref> Five days later, on 10 February, he scored his first professional goal while playing for Jong Ajax in an Eerste Divisie match away against FC Den Bosch.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-02-13 |title=Samenvatting FC Den Bosch – Jong Ajax {{!}} Geen zege voor Ajacieden |url=https://www.ajax.nl/artikelen/samenvatting-fc-den-bosch-jong-ajax-geen-zege-voor-ajacieden |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=www.ajax.nl |language=nl}}</ref> Hato quickly gained more first-team opportunities and started the [[2023 KNVB Cup final]] against [[PSV Eindhoven]] on 30 April 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2023/04/ajax-1-1-psv-eindhoven-2-3-pens-psv-triumph-in-final-of-few-chances/|website=Dutchnews.nl|date=30 April 2023|accessdate=2 May 2023|title= Ajax 1–1 PSV Eindhoven (2–3 pens): PSV triumph in final of few chances}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.espn.in/football/lineups/_/gameId/668068|website=ESPN|title=AJAX 1–1 PSV|date=30 April 2023|accessdate=1 May 2023}}</ref> Following his debut season, Hato was awarded the [[List of AFC Ajax records and statistics#AFC Ajax prize winners|Abdelhak Nouri Trophy]] as the most talented player from Ajax's youth academy.<ref name="auto">{{cite web |title=Abdelhak Nouri Trofee voor Jorrel Hato |url=https://www.ajax.nl/artikelen/abdelhak-nouri-trofee-voor-jorrel-hato/ |publisher=AFC Ajax |access-date=5 June 2023 |language=nl |date=5 June 2023}}</ref>

====2023–2025: First-team regular and vice-captain====
[[File:Jorrel Hato.jpg|right|thumb|upright|Hato with [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in 2024.]]
Hato became an undisputed starter and key player for Ajax at the beginning of the [[2023–24 AFC Ajax season|2023–24 season]]. Despite the team's struggles, the 17-year-old played almost every minute of the campaign across all competitions,<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|783173}}</ref> earning praise for his consistent performances and maturity. In October 2023, he was named by English newspaper ''[[The Guardian]]'' as one of the best players born in 2006 worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2023/oct/11/next-generation-2023-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football|title=Next Generation 2023: 60 of the best young talents in world football|first1=Marcus|last1=Christenson|first2=Steven|last2=Bloor|first3=Garry|last3=Blight|date=11 October 2023|access-date=11 October 2023|website=theguardian.com}}</ref> He scored his first senior goal for Ajax against [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] on 25 November 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-25 |title=Verslag {{!}} Ajax kent geen genade met hekkensluiter Vitesse |url=https://www.ajax.nl/artikelen/verslag-ajax-kent-geen-genade-met-hekkensluiter-vitesse |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=www.ajax.nl |language=nl}}</ref> Following the departure of [[Davy Klaassen]] and [[Dušan Tadić]], and injuries to [[Steven Bergwijn]] and [[Steven Berghuis]], Hato was appointed as one of the team's vice-captains. On 14 December 2023, he captained Ajax against [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]], becoming the club's youngest-ever captain in a European match at 17 years and 282 days old.<ref name="AjaxCaptain2">{{cite web |date=12 May 2024 |title=Jorrel Hato is Talent of the Year |url=https://english.ajax.nl/articles/jorrel-hato-is-talent-of-the-year |access-date=1 April 2025 |website=Ajax.nl |language=nl}}</ref> In recognition of his rapid development and importance, Hato signed a new contract extension with Ajax on 12 March 2024, keeping him at the club until June 2028.<ref name=":0" />

Hato continued his role as a key defender in the [[2024–25 AFC Ajax season|2024–25 season]] under new manager [[Francesco Farioli]], playing primarily at centre-back but also providing cover at left-back.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2025-06-17 |title=Farioli: Leaving Ajax, eyeing a move to manage in Italy |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/farioli-leaving-ajax-eyeing-move-135600107.html |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en |agency=OneFootball}}</ref> He contributed offensively as well, scoring twice in the Eredivisie and once in the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] by mid-March 2025. At the end of the season, he was named [[Eredivisie Awards#Johan Cruyff Talent of the Year|Eredivisie Talent of the Year]].<ref name="Eredivisie TOTY">{{Cite web |url=https://eredivisie.eu/news/sem-steijn-and-renate-jansen-big-winners-at-the-eredivisie-awards/ |title=Sem Steijn and Renate Jansen big winners at the Eredivisie Awards |website=eredivisie.eu |date=26 May 2025 |access-date=26 May 2025}}</ref>

===Chelsea===
On 3 August 2025, Hato joined [[Premier League]] club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] signing a seven-year contract for an initial fee of £35.5m.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jorrel Hato joins Chelsea! |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/jorrel-hato-joins-chelsea |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=www.chelseafc.com |language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Jorrel Haro transfer news: Chelsea sign teenage defender fron Ajax for an initial £35.5m plus add-ons|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11668/13405232/jorrel-hato-transfer-news-chelsea-sign-teenage-defender-from-ajax-for-an-initial-35-5m-plus-add-ons|access-date=3 August 2025 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=3 August 2025}}</ref> On 10 January 2026, he scored his first goal for Chelsea, the opener in a 5–1 away win against [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] in the [[2025-26 FA Cup#Third round|FA Cup Third Round]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Miranda |first=Fellipe |date=2026-01-10 |title=Charlton 1-5 Chelsea, FA Cup: Post-match reaction |url=https://weaintgotnohistory.sbnation.com/domestic-cups/165028/charlton-athletic-1-5-chelsea-fa-cup-post-match-reaction |access-date=2026-01-11 |website=We Ain't Got No History |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
In November 2021, he was included in the [[Netherlands national under-16 football team|Dutch under-16]] squad.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-11-09 |title=Tijn den Boggende in voorselectie Oranje Onder 16 |url=https://www.fcutrecht.nl/nieuws/2021/november/tijn-den-boggende-in-voorselectie-oranje-onder-16/ |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=FC Utrecht |language=nl}}</ref> He became captain of the under-16 Dutch team in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fussballtransfers.com/amp4138466729366403561-profivertrag-fuer-ajax-talent|title=Profivertrag für Ajax-Talent|website=fussballtransfers.com}}</ref>

After brief spells with the U17 and U21 teams, Hato was called up to the senior [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] matches against [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] and [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] in November 2023.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal-mannen/81128/hato-maakt-debuut-oranjeselectie |title=Hato maakt debuut in Oranjeselectie |trans-title=Hato debuts in national team squad |language=Dutch |date=10 November 2023 |access-date=15 November 2023}}</ref> He made his debut on 21 November 2023 as a half-time substitute for [[Virgil van Dijk]] in the 6–0 win against Gibraltar.<ref>{{Cite web |title='Trots dat ik op zo'n jonge leeftijd mag debuteren' |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal-mannen/81164/trots-dat-ik-op-zon-jonge-leeftijd-mag-debuteren |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=www.onsoranje.nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Zes goals voor Oranje tegen Gibraltar op avond vol primeurs |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal-mannen/81163/ruime-zege-oranje-op-avond-vol-primeurs |access-date=2025-08-03 |website=www.onsoranje.nl}}</ref> Following his debut, Hato continued to be part of the senior setup, earning four more caps during 2024.<ref name="soccerway" /> His sixth cap came as a substitute in the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A#Quarter-finals|UEFA Nations League Finals quarter-final]] second leg against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] on 23 March 2025.<ref name="EUFoot">{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=32560|title=Jorrel Hato|website=EU-Football.info|access-date=1 April 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Hato was born in the Netherlands to a Curaçaoan father and Cape Verdean mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.helden.media/verhalen/jorrel-hato-mijn-tijd-komt-nog-wel/|title=Jorrel Hato: 'Mijn tijd komt nog wel'|first=Martijn van|last=Weesenbeek|date=16 June 2025}}</ref>

